stylometry: Sensitivity analysis is a technique that is used to determine how different values of an independent variable will impact a particular dependent variable.  It also can provide a different answer for an already solved problem.  You can take the changing cell which is the input and change the setting to get a different solution.  Sensitivity analysis is important because you can have more than one answer in some models, and with using this sensitivity analysis, it allows to to see all the different answers you get.
